atinized version (ostensibly representing a diminutive of Latin <i>niger</i> ‘black’) of the vernacular <i>Ni(h)el</i>, i.e.   Neil .  Although it is frequently found in medieval records, this form was probably not used in everyday life before its revival by antiquarians such as  Sir Walter  Scott in the 19th century."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705192,"age":7,"year":"1328","julianDay":2206102,"title":"First War of Scottish Independence","description":"The First War of Scottish Independence began after England invaded Scotland in 1296. The Treaty of Edinburgh was signed in 1328 which declared peace between the two kingdoms and brought the war to an end.","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705193,"age":16,"year":"1337","toYear":"1453","julianDay":2209390,"title":"The Hundred Years' War","description":"The Hundred Years' War between France and England was largely due to the question of legitimate succession to the French crown.","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705195,"age":61,"year":"1382","julianDay":2225826,"title":"Wycliffe's Bible","description":"John Wycliffe, English theologian and professor at the University of Oxford, completed a translation of the Bible from the Latin Vulgate into Middle English. This translation is known as Wycliffe's Bible and was completed around 1382.","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wycliffe%27s_Bible","urlTitle":"Wikipedia - Wycliffe's Bible","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"When Nigel Loring was born on 23 April 1320, in Chalgrave, Bedfordshire, England, his father, Roger Loring, was 30 and his mother, Cassandra Perrott, was 26. He married Margaret Beaupel in Devon, England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 1 daughter. In 1348, at the age of 28, his occupation is listed as knight of the garter. He died on 18 March 1386, in his hometown, at the age of 65, and was buried in Chalgrave, Bedfordshire, England."},"et":{"23 April 1320–18 March 1386":"23. aprill 1320–18. märts 1386","1320–1385":"1320–1385","